      "writtenOn": "2018-10-20T00:11:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry, this was from the *AEMU implementation above where we first decide whether or not we even need to call the API on the host; that is, we do not need to call the API if access was to invalidate the range, or invalidate the entire buffer itself. That\u0027s because when we invalidate the range, we are asking to discard the existing contents of the buffer. When we are emulating glMapBufferRange, only when we are not discarding do we need to actually run the same API on the host to discover the current contents of the buffer.",
